                    <msContents>
                        <summary>
                            <p>This is the MS. "(16) A. 43" described on pp. 23-26 (555-558) of
                                Further Notes. It was one of seven (originally marked W. 113 and W.
                                124-129) bought of J. J. Naaman in September, 1901, comprises 134
                                ff. of 17.5 x 12.2 c. and 17 ll., and is written in a small, neat
                                Turkish riq'a, undated. Its chief contents are the Bishárat-náma of
                                Rafi'i (ff. 11b-54a), the Hidáyat-náma of Firishta-záda (ff.
                                89b-112b), the Ganj-náma of Rafi'i (f. 115b-120a), and finally the
                                Shakriyár-náma of Panáhi (f. 121b-131a), composed in 860/1456.</p>
                        </summary>
